1
00:00:14,041 --> 00:00:16,583
♪

2
00:00:16,666 --> 00:00:17,791
[GONZALEZ]
Nine years ago,

3
00:00:17,875 --> 00:00:20,083
the War of Unification
came to an end.

4
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:23,458
Golbarn Helwise,
the king of Cidal,

5
00:00:23,541 --> 00:00:25,916
surrendered his crown
to the emperor.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,583
He became Prime Minister.
The following year,

7
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:32,416
Golbarn was officially
installed in the position.

8
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,791
In addition, five men who played
significant roles in the war

9
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:37,375
were granted territories,

10
00:00:37,458 --> 00:00:39,916
along with titles
in the new government.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,708
They were named
the Five Dukes.

12
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:46,041
However, this newly
established system

13
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:47,833
was not destined to last long.

14
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:52,666
Patrick Starry, Duke of Widonia,

15
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:54,708
was apprehended
as the ringleader of a plot

16
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:56,958
to assassinate
the prime minister.

17
00:00:57,041 --> 00:01:00,166
Just before his trial,
he was poisoned and perished.

18
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,708
The Duke of Nova, Ewan Breeze.

19
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:06,208
So offended at being
suspected of rebellion,

20
00:01:06,291 --> 00:01:09,125
he actually decided
to incite an insurrection.

21
00:01:09,208 --> 00:01:12,375
This hero of the war, one of
the renowned Seven Knights,

22
00:01:12,458 --> 00:01:13,875
was killed while fighting.

23
00:01:13,958 --> 00:01:17,291
Umar Jujuman,
the Duke of Littroke.

24
00:01:17,375 --> 00:01:20,208
Despite being a sworn friend
of Prime Minister Golbarn

25
00:01:20,291 --> 00:01:23,708
during the war, his paranoia
ultimately proved stronger

26
00:01:23,791 --> 00:01:25,666
and led him to stage a revolt.

27
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:27,500
He failed and was executed.

28
00:01:31,166 --> 00:01:33,416
[gulping]

29
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:36,333
[GONZALEZ sighs]

30
00:01:36,416 --> 00:01:39,833
They say the only way to attain
peace is through sacrifice.

31
00:01:39,916 --> 00:01:41,375
Right.

32
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:45,291
[RYLAN]
It was a huge mistake.

33
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:47,500
They should have never
named those five Dukes

34
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,250
or given them any territory.

35
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,083
Of course they were
rewarded with titles

36
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,666
while the real heroes
on the front line

37
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,416
were completely overlooked.

38
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:56,750
[scoffs] I don’t know what
heroes you’re talking about.

39
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,541
-Can it, you old bastard!
-[MARLYA gasps]

40
00:01:58,625 --> 00:02:00,458
You’re an old fart, same as me!

41
00:02:00,541 --> 00:02:01,875
Say that again!
See what happens!

42
00:02:01,958 --> 00:02:03,416
[RYLAN]
You’re the one who started it!

43
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,375
[MARLYA] You know what?
I think both of you are young!

44
00:02:06,458 --> 00:02:08,458
-You mean it?
-Course she does!

45
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,916
Yep. Real children.

46
00:02:12,208 --> 00:02:13,666
[sighing]

47
00:02:15,375 --> 00:02:17,041
Only seven days left.

48
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:19,125
Then it’ll be ten years
since the war ended.

49
00:02:19,208 --> 00:02:22,458
Seems like only
a distant memory now.

50
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:24,083
Almost a dream.

51
00:02:24,166 --> 00:02:25,666
Then again...

52
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:28,208
Duke Littroke wasn’t
killed that long ago.

53
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:29,500
Just over a year.

54
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:31,875
So only two of em are left.

55
00:02:31,958 --> 00:02:35,208
Shwarz Diese.
The Duke of Hybranz.

56
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,666
And Kal-O’s Duke.
Ray Dawn.

57
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,500
♪

58
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,208
[door opens]

59
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:58,750
Hmm. You’re looking well.

60
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,416
As are you.

61
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,166
[iron rattling]

62
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:43,000
[SERGE] All right, buddy.
In you go.

63
00:04:43,083 --> 00:04:44,583
[SWINDLER grunts]

64
00:04:44,666 --> 00:04:46,541
[SWINDLER] Hey, hey, hey!
Hold on a minute!

65
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:47,958
Look, is it so wrong for me

66
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:50,333
to try and earn
a little bread on the side?

67
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:51,583
When you try and make it seem

68
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:53,583
as though you own
a fairy primordial?

69
00:04:53,666 --> 00:04:56,083
Yes, it’s very illegal.

70
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:00,750
[SWINDLER sighs]

71
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:04,041
Dammit!
Yow! Ah!

72
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:16,333
Exceptional quality
despite its age.

73
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:21,500
[metal clinking]

74
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:25,916
[CHASE]
Hmm.

75
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,750
It may just be an empty casing,

76
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:29,833
but if it is genuine,
then it’s illegal.

77
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:33,208
[CHASE] Excuse me.
A word, if I might.

78
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,250
[SHOPKEEPER]
D-Dorothea?

79
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:35,541
Hey, you’ve got the wrong idea!

80
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:37,083
That thing outside is, uh.

81
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,041
[MARLYA]
So those are the new models?

82
00:05:58,875 --> 00:06:00,958
I’ve been seeing them a lot.

83
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:03,208
[FREE]
You mean the Zern Ones?

84
00:06:03,291 --> 00:06:05,583
[MARLYA]
Improved artificial fairies.

85
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,625
They’re much different
than the older ones.

86
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:10,083
Their grand debut
is coming up soon.

87
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:12,625
They’ll be security at the
war anniversary ceremony.

88
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:15,791
But more preliminary testing
is needed before then.

89
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:18,083
You mean like a rehearsal
before the event?

90
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:19,791
[tones sounding]

91
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:21,875
[GIRL screams]

92
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:22,958
What the?

93
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:27,291
-[metal rattling]
-[GIRL whimpers]

94
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,333
No!

95
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,625
[whistles]

96
00:06:32,708 --> 00:06:34,791
Damn! It’s not
listening to my commands!

97
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:36,750
♪

98
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,375
[tones sounding]

99
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:43,666
-Protect them!
-On it!

100
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,541
[OPERATOR] Why can’t I?
It’s malfunctioning!

101
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:48,208
Allow me!

102
00:06:49,958 --> 00:06:50,958
Come on!

103
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,750
Activate the other two, quick!

104
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,708
[whistles]

105
00:06:58,791 --> 00:07:00,791
♪

106
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,416
[tone sounding]

107
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:13,250
[OPERATOR panting]

108
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:17,166
[sighing]

109
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:20,000
-[GIRL crying]
-Everything’s all right, now.

110
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:22,041
Thank you for
saving my daughter!

111
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,750
[FREE] Were you able to pinpoint
the cause of the malfunction?

112
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:34,375
Greetings.
Dorothea, yes?

113
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,875
-Hello.
-You’re from the Ministry?

114
00:07:36,958 --> 00:07:38,791
Correct. Griff Mercer.

115
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,458
You wouldn’t know it, but he’s
the assistant vice-minister.

116
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:43,750
Oh? So you’re
high ranking then.

117
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,750
I wish it was more glamorous,

118
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,125
but you’ll note
the “assistant” in my title.

119
00:07:48,208 --> 00:07:49,791
I’m an errand boy.

120
00:07:49,875 --> 00:07:51,500
[MECHANIC]
I heard you two were present

121
00:07:51,583 --> 00:07:52,958
when this thing went berserk?

122
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,458
[FREE]
Yes, that’s correct.

123
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:55,958
I’m assuming you’re
with the military?

124
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:58,791
Just a civilian mechanic
under their employment.

125
00:07:58,875 --> 00:08:02,041
You can call me Hanns.
And this one here is Ted.

126
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:04,000
My faithful right-hand man,
if you will.

127
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,458
[FREE] Hmm.

128
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:07,291
Hanns is head of
the Maintenance Division

129
00:08:07,375 --> 00:08:09,166
and happens to be one of
the most exceptional

130
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:11,208
artificial fairy technicians
alive.

131
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:13,458
[HANNS chuckles] Compliments
will get you nowhere.

132
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,916
[GRIFF chuckles]

133
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,416
[sniffing]

134
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,833
[MARLYA]
So, what did you find?

135
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:21,708
[TED] Our inspection turned up
nothing unusual.

136
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,375
[GRIFF sighs]
To be straightforward,

137
00:08:23,458 --> 00:08:26,458
I’m not sure my superiors
are going to accept that answer.

138
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:27,916
We were phasing out

139
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,166
the older Psyden
Seven models completely,

140
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,875
which have been in use
since the War of Unification.

141
00:08:32,958 --> 00:08:34,250
And the brand new Zern Ones

142
00:08:34,333 --> 00:08:36,250
were supposed to be
their replacement.

143
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:39,166
Well this is a headache.

144
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:42,333
-That’s an understatement.
-One other thing.

145
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:44,333
Huh?

146
00:08:44,416 --> 00:08:46,083
[horse whinnies]

147
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:50,250
[NEIN] We received info
from a certain source

148
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,958
regarding the Black Fairy Tome.

149
00:08:52,041 --> 00:08:54,250
When we were over
at East End Base,

150
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:55,833
Assistant
Vice-Minister Griff

151
00:08:55,916 --> 00:08:58,958
mentioned there’d been
some sort of new development.

152
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:00,708
The timing couldn’t be better.

153
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:03,000
The one you obtained
in Isharot was a fake,

154
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:05,750
but this time,
it could be the real thing.

155
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,666
I’ll be sending Marlya
to retrieve it.

156
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,625
Just me?
Who’s my partner then?

157
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:13,541
There isn’t anything
to worry about.

158
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:15,333
She’s a pro.

159
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:18,250
♪

160
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:21,208
Oh wow.

161
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:27,666
[KLARA] I’ve never been
to this city before either.

162
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,833
[MARLYA]
Hopefully we don’t get lost.

163
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:33,416
We saw the map,
so I don’t see how we could.

164
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:34,958
[MARLYA groans]

165
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:37,166
[horse neighs]

166
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:42,583
[bar chatter]

167
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:47,875
[nervous laughter]

168
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:49,958
♪

169
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:56,875
I assume you’re Buz,

170
00:09:56,958 --> 00:09:58,416
the informant
we’re supposed to meet?

171
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:06,250
[chuckles]

172
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:11,833
It is my understanding,
you’ve been well paid.

173
00:10:11,916 --> 00:10:14,083
Whatever information you have,
let’s hear it.

174
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:19,833
About that, the advance payment
wasn’t enough.

175
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,958
You’ll need to sweeten
the deal somehow.

176
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:23,416
[MARLYA groans]

177
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:26,875
But if you little Dorothea
bitches prefer to fight.

178
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:28,250
[BUZ snaps]

179
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:30,333
[shouting]

180
00:10:30,416 --> 00:10:31,416
[MAN groans]

181
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,750
♪

182
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:35,458
[grunting]

183
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,291
[grunting]

184
00:10:43,291 --> 00:10:44,458
Ah!

185
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:49,916
[HENCHMAN]
Boss!

186
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,208
[BUZ breathing shakily]

187
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:57,500
[chuckles]

188
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:01,083
Relax!

189
00:11:01,166 --> 00:11:03,416
Don’t you two know a joke
when you hear one?

190
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,958
Huh? Huh?

191
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:06,750
One more time.

192
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,500
Tell us what you know.

193
00:11:08,583 --> 00:11:09,750
Sure.

194
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,291
My pleasure.

195
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:25,708
[CHASE]
Think hard.

196
00:11:25,791 --> 00:11:28,500
You noticed nothing unusual
about the artificial fairy?

197
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,375
[OPERATOR sighs]

198
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,666
If there was,
I didn’t have a clue.

199
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:36,958
Thank you for your time.

200
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:42,166
Must be a defect.

201
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:45,125
Or somebody sabotaged it
without us knowing.

202
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:47,750
I doubt anyone on the outside
would be able to tamper

203
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,875
with a military-grade
artificial fairy.

204
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:51,416
-Huh?
-[FREE] Hmm?

205
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:53,875
Daniel?

206
00:11:53,958 --> 00:11:56,583
A former colleague,
I take it, Chase?

207
00:11:56,666 --> 00:12:00,458
Yeah. I think he’s still
assigned to the Security Bureau.

208
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:02,458
-Give me a minute, sir.
-Sure.

209
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:09,666
♪

210
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:33,333
Something keeps nagging
at me, but what is it?

211
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,791
I’m your loyal subject,
at your command!

212
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:39,791
Girls, whatever you need,
just name it!

213
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:41,458
That’s a switch.

214
00:12:41,541 --> 00:12:44,041
Since you offered, we’ll need
a vehicle for two people.

215
00:12:44,125 --> 00:12:47,041
No problem, boss!
It’s done! One sec.

216
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:52,416
Hey! You’re moving up, Boss.

217
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,666
[BUZ] There was an auction
recently held in the city.

218
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:03,750
It was there the actual Black
Fairy Tome was put up for sale.

219
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,916
They referred to it
as “The Black Four”

220
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,541
or something to that effect.

221
00:13:07,625 --> 00:13:10,375
Most of the attendees were
bidding huge sums of money,

222
00:13:10,458 --> 00:13:12,000
trying to win the prize.

223
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:15,416
But in the end, the highest
amount was from an agent

224
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,916
who’s no stranger
to these kinds of circles.

225
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,458
A man. Goes by the name Dice.

226
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,375
-Look. That the guy?
-[inhales sharply]

227
00:13:25,458 --> 00:13:26,500
[KLARA]
Yes.

228
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,416
♪

229
00:13:41,541 --> 00:13:43,416
-Hang on.
-Got it.

230
00:13:51,375 --> 00:13:53,375
♪

231
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,000
♪

232
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,541
-It’s about to leave!
-We’ll make it!

233
00:14:16,625 --> 00:14:18,125
Dorothea.

234
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:21,000
-We’re in pursuit of a suspect.
-[ATTENDANT] Understood.

235
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:23,666
-Please go on through.
-Much appreciated.

236
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:24,750
Thank you.

237
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:28,375
[whistle blowing]

238
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:32,625
♪

239
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:35,833
-[whistle blowing]
-[groans]

240
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:37,500
-Hurry it up!
-[MAN gasps]

241
00:14:37,583 --> 00:14:39,708
Or I’ll punch your ticket,
you get me?

242
00:14:41,208 --> 00:14:42,625
We’re boarding!

243
00:14:43,708 --> 00:14:46,375
-Official Dorothea business.
-Oh, yes, ma’am!

244
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:50,208
[horn blowing]

245
00:14:50,291 --> 00:14:53,333
Train for Rondacia!
Now departing!

246
00:14:53,416 --> 00:14:56,416
[horn continues]

247
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,083
Just a moment, madame,
I’m sorry.

248
00:14:58,166 --> 00:15:02,666
-You want my ticket? Here!
-Your admission isn’t the issue.

249
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:04,875
[horn blowing]

250
00:15:04,958 --> 00:15:06,208
[gasps]

251
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:07,791
I’m afraid the train’s
already left.

252
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,166
[SWEETIE growls]

253
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:16,416
Bitter Sweet, too.
It wasn’t just Dorothea.

254
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,000
Seems Gui Carlin also
had information pertaining

255
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:20,750
to the Black Four’s location.

256
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:25,041
♪

257
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:46,000
Nothing.

258
00:15:46,083 --> 00:15:48,583
I could’ve sworn
he got on this train.

259
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:51,041
[horn blowing]

260
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:53,791
-Have any luck?
-Mm-mm.

261
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:55,333
Let’s check once more.

262
00:15:55,416 --> 00:15:56,541
Right.

263
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:02,458
He doesn’t seem
to be on board.

264
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:04,125
We should check
the freight car too.

265
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:07,208
[KLARA] You can’t enter or exit
while we’re in motion.

266
00:16:07,291 --> 00:16:08,791
Isn’t the train’s next stop

267
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:11,166
coming up at a station
called Sharbit?

268
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:13,666
[KLARA] When we arrive, let's
have the attendant open it.

269
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,458
We’ll check the interior then.

270
00:16:21,916 --> 00:16:24,458
[MARLYA] So, Klara, this is
the first mission

271
00:16:24,541 --> 00:16:27,250
I’ve gone on where
it’s just been you and me.

272
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:28,708
I’m curious.

273
00:16:29,958 --> 00:16:32,166
How did you end up in Dorothea?

274
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,666
I joined willingly.

275
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,750
♪

276
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,125
[KLARA] My entire family
was lost in the war.

277
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,125
[breathing shakily]

278
00:16:49,125 --> 00:16:50,500
-[NEIN] That's far enough!
-[SOLDIER] Huh?

279
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:53,041
[MEN grunting]

280
00:16:55,708 --> 00:16:57,125
[gasps]

281
00:16:57,208 --> 00:17:00,583
[KLARA] Then she came along.
Director Nein.

282
00:17:00,666 --> 00:17:02,333
She saved my life.

283
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,416
♪

284
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:07,375
[laughs softly]

285
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:10,166
[chuckles]

286
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,458
It hasn’t been easy for you.

287
00:17:15,916 --> 00:17:17,833
The war destroyed
many people’s lives.

288
00:17:18,916 --> 00:17:20,208
Both my parents.

289
00:17:20,291 --> 00:17:21,708
They died before
I got the chance

290
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,500
to know either one of them.

291
00:17:26,041 --> 00:17:28,625
[KLARA] In that case,
I guess that makes me fortunate.

292
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:29,583
[MARLYA gasps]

293
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:31,125
I’m grateful.

294
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:32,791
Even though
I lost mine, too,

295
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,291
at least I have memories.

296
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:36,375
♪

297
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,375
[cries softly]

298
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:44,000
[horn blowing]

299
00:17:45,916 --> 00:17:48,541
Are you getting off
at the next station?

300
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:50,041
[MAN chuckles]

301
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:53,833
Ha!

302
00:17:53,916 --> 00:17:55,625
You made his day, mister.

303
00:17:58,125 --> 00:18:00,291
[brakes screeching, hissing]

304
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:04,083
-[KLARA] Sharbit Station!
-[MARLYA] Let’s hurry!

305
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:06,583
[KLARA]
If you would.

306
00:18:13,166 --> 00:18:15,166
-He’s not here.
-How’d we miss him?

307
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:21,875
The briefcase!

308
00:18:21,958 --> 00:18:23,625
♪

309
00:18:25,125 --> 00:18:27,458
-Don’t let that man get away!
-[MAN] Huh?

310
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:32,416
Let’s split up!

311
00:18:33,791 --> 00:18:34,833
Stop right there!

312
00:18:39,041 --> 00:18:40,083
He’s gone.

313
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:45,166
♪

314
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:53,125
-[metal clicks]
-[gasps]

315
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:57,500
You’re coming with us.
Hands up in the air.

316
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:03,958
[chuckles]

317
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:16,083
Seriously? How long are you
going to keep this up?

318
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:23,541
-Anything?
-He’s stonewalling us.

319
00:19:23,625 --> 00:19:26,583
Even if we tried getting him to
talk by breaking a limb or two,

320
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:28,791
I doubt it would
make a difference.

321
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,041
[KLARA]
He didn’t have anything

322
00:19:30,125 --> 00:19:32,416
resembling the Black Fairy
Tome on him.

323
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:35,208
But he’s supposed to be the one
who won it at the auction.

324
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:37,291
If he’s acting as an agent,

325
00:19:37,375 --> 00:19:39,916
he must’ve been bidding
on someone else’s behalf.

326
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,416
Whoever it is, I doubt he’s
going to open up about it.

327
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:43,708
[SERGE] There you are!

328
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,166
-I missed you, Klara!
-[KLARA groans]

329
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,916
So how’d the mission go?

330
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
I bet you were
lonely without me.

331
00:19:49,083 --> 00:19:52,708
-It was quieter.
-Aw! I missed you too!

332
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:58,000
[MARLYA]
That malfunctioning Zern One,

333
00:19:58,083 --> 00:19:59,958
did they find out
what’s wrong with it?

334
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:03,041
[FREE] We haven’t discovered
anything out of the ordinary.

335
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:05,208
[MARLYA] And Dice isn’t
cooperating with us.

336
00:20:06,541 --> 00:20:07,833
What next?

337
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:10,333
[chuckling]

338
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,791
-Axel? You!
-Hold it right there!

339
00:20:12,875 --> 00:20:14,000
[hissing]

340
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:16,375
[AXEL]
Everyone! Take it down a notch!

341
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:20,291
-[AXEL groaning]
-Oh. Right.

342
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:22,208
I almost forgot--you were shot.

343
00:20:22,291 --> 00:20:24,166
And I nearly died, too.

344
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:25,875
I tell you,
that woman’s cold-blooded.

345
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:27,666
Shooting me in the back!

346
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:30,333
-I’m surprised you’re alive.
-[AXEL chuckles]

347
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:31,750
I still manage to get around,

348
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:34,125
especially when I need
to see my good friends.

349
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:35,833
-Uh-huh.
-That last time?

350
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:38,125
I had no idea
you were going to be there.

351
00:20:38,208 --> 00:20:41,291
Blind luck.
It could happen to anyone.

352
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:43,125
So what do you say?
No hard feelings?

353
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:45,708
[FREE] Whatever.
I’ve got a full plate right now.

354
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:48,541
With the anniversary
of the war coming up, right?

355
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:50,333
I’m sure you’re prepared.

356
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:54,333
But if you need any help at all,
be sure to let ‘ol Axel know.

357
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:57,041
Then again, you do know
an awful lot of people

358
00:20:57,125 --> 00:20:58,958
and have a habit
of hearing too much.

359
00:21:04,416 --> 00:21:06,625
[AXEL]
Well, well. Dice.

360
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,083
Do you know him?

361
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:11,541
[AXEL] He’s famous.
In certain circles.

362
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:14,208
A real professional
who doesn’t talk much.

363
00:21:14,291 --> 00:21:16,458
Who employs him?

364
00:21:16,541 --> 00:21:18,708
[AXEL] It’s rare for an agent
of his caliber to be hired

365
00:21:18,791 --> 00:21:20,500
by only a single client.

366
00:21:21,791 --> 00:21:24,666
But, according to rumor,

367
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,750
Dice usually
works for one man.

368
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:34,333
♪

369
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:39,416
Gilbert Warlock.
We need to chat.

370
00:23:10,291 --> 00:23:12,291
[BOHME] Thank you for the meal,
but if you’ll excuse me,

371
00:23:12,375 --> 00:23:14,250
Duke Diese,
I must be on my way.

372
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:17,500
But, Military Minister,
you’ve only arrived.

373
00:23:17,583 --> 00:23:19,833
Why not stay a little
while longer?

374
00:23:19,916 --> 00:23:21,875
I’m afraid that’s out
of the question.

375
00:23:21,958 --> 00:23:24,000
[DIESE]
I hope it’s nothing serious.

376
00:23:26,208 --> 00:23:27,791
You must keep this between us.

377
00:23:29,125 --> 00:23:30,541
The fact is...

378
00:23:30,625 --> 00:23:32,708
there’s been a malfunction
with a Zern One model.

379
00:23:32,791 --> 00:23:33,708
Oh!

380
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,208
What terrible news.

381
00:23:39,375 --> 00:23:41,125
[HANNS] Look at the state
this Zern is in.

382
00:23:41,208 --> 00:23:42,916
[CHASE] It's painful,
suspecting someone close.

383
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,541
[WOLF]
Don’t worry.

384
00:23:44,625 --> 00:23:46,416
[SWEETIE] They're standing
right here. This is my present.

385
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:48,416
[NEIN]
Ears within Gui Carlin, eh?

